{"key":"processedPost-9412441","value":{"id":9412441,"first":9411545,"last":9413204,"when":1229022904,"utime":"12/11/08 09:15 PM","content":"After the mist evaporates, mist again about 2 hours later.&nbsp; This wetting of the substrate, and then drying, is a major pinning trigger.&nbsp; It's not as big as lots of fresh air exchange, but it's more important than maintaining a constant 99% humidity.&nbsp; You can get a decent mechanical hygrometer for under $20.&nbsp; Google <i>mechanical hygrometer</i>.&nbsp; Disregard all the threads you find saying digitals are better.&nbsp; They're not using them in near-saturation humidity.<br />RR","title":"Re: Misting/Shotgun FC Problems Possibly. Help Please"}}